            "html": "<p class=\"q-text qu-display--block\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-bottom: 1em; overflow-wrap: anywhere; word-break: break-word; direction: ltr; text-align: start;\"><span style=\"font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; background: none;\">Hi,</span></p> <p class=\"q-text qu-display--block\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-bottom: 1em; overflow-wrap: anywhere; word-break: break-word; direction: ltr; text-align: start;\"><span style=\"font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; background: none;\">I would suggest the following points for any beginner in bodybuilding:</span></p> <p class=\"q-text qu-display--block\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-bottom: 1em; overflow-wrap: anywhere; word-break: break-word; direction: ltr; text-align: start;\"><span style=\"font-weight: bold; font-style: normal; background: none;\">(1) Mindset</span><span style=\"font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; background: none;\">: The first and most important tip is to have a success mindset. Don’t give lame excuses to yourself for skipping workouts. Have full faith in yourself that you will succeed in achieving your goal.</span></p> <p class=\"q-text qu-display--block\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-bottom: 1em; overflow-wrap: anywhere; word-break: break-word; direction: ltr; text-align: start;\"><span style=\"font-weight: bold; font-style: normal; background: none;\">(2) Goal</span><span style=\"font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; background: none;\">: The second most important point is to set a specific and clear goal. Ask yourself a question, what do you want to achieve with bodybuilding?</span></p> <p class=\"q-text qu-display--block\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-bottom: 1em; overflow-wrap: anywhere; word-break: break-word; direction: ltr; text-align: start;\"><span style=\"font-weight: bold; font-style: normal; background: none;\">(3) Good instructor</span><span style=\"font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; background: none;\">: Look out for an instructor with proven record of training people.</span></p> <p class=\"q-text qu-display--block\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-bottom: 1em; overflow-wrap: anywhere; word-break: break-word; direction: ltr; text-align: start;\"><span style=\"font-weight: bold; font-style: normal; background: none;\">(4) Plan</span><span style=\"font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; background: none;\">: Once you have set out a goal, next step is to plan the steps to achieve that result. Obviously, there may be some changes in the plan at later stages but you should have a plan from the very start. Planning will have two important parts:</span></p> <p class=\"q-text qu-display--block\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-bottom: 1em; overflow-wrap: anywhere; word-break: break-word; direction: ltr; text-align: start;\"><span style=\"font-weight: bold; font-style: normal; background: none;\">a) Plan your workout</span><span style=\"font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; background: none;\">: You can ask your trainer in the Gym to guide you to the best workouts for beginners. However when I started, I did complete body exercises every two days (As per the instructions of my coach). This continued for 14 days and then changed to Push- Pull- Leg and then One body part each day. My favourite is Push-Pull-Leg.</span></p> <p class=\"q-text qu-display--block\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-bottom: 1em; overflow-wrap: anywhere; word-break: break-word; direction: ltr; text-align: start;\"><span style=\"font-weight: bold; font-style: normal; background: none;\">b) Plan your diet</span><span style=\"font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; background: none;\">: Every bodybuilder will tell you that a proper diet is the core of bodybuilding and this is true. You should drink plenty of water throughout the day and focus on adequate intake of Fibre, Carbohydrate, Healthy fats and Protein. The amount of protein should be 1.2 to 2 grams per Kg of your body weight per day.</span></p> <p class=\"q-text qu-display--block\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-bottom: 1em; overflow-wrap: anywhere; word-break: break-word; direction: ltr; text-align: start;\"><span style=\"font-weight: bold; font-style: normal; background: none;\">(5) Avoid injuries</span><span style=\"font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; background: none;\">: Do not try to become a hero on the very first day of your workout by lifting heavy weights. Remember, you cannot build muscles in one day, but by working out consistently over a period of time. Increase the weights gradually as per your body capacity.</span></p> <p class=\"q-text qu-display--block\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-bottom: 1em; overflow-wrap: anywhere; word-break: break-word; direction: ltr; text-align: start;\"><span style=\"font-weight: bold; font-style: normal; background: none;\">(6) Motivation and consistency</span><span style=\"font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; background: none;\">: Once the motivation is gone, people start skipping the workouts. Write down a note and paste it on a wall where you can see it daily (note should mention whatever motivated you for bodybuilding in the first place).</span></p> <p class=\"q-text qu-display--block\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-bottom: 1em; overflow-wrap: anywhere; word-break: break-word; direction: ltr; text-align: start;\"><span style=\"font-weight: bold; font-style: normal; background: none;\">(7) Ask for feedback from coach</span><span style=\"font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; background: none;\">: Normally if you don’t have a personal instructor, you will have to go and ask for his feedback and improvements. Ask him if you need any improvements, he will probably highlight them in case of incorrect exercise form and other mistakes. (Mostly applicable in India)</span></p> <p class=\"q-text qu-display--block\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-bottom: 1em; overflow-wrap: anywhere; word-break: break-word; direction: ltr; text-align: start;\"><span style=\"font-weight: bold; font-style: normal; background: none;\">(8) Correct form of exercise</span><span style=\"font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; background: none;\">: Focus on the correct form of exercise and get feedback from your coach/instructor.</span></p> <p class=\"q-text qu-display--block\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-bottom: 1em; overflow-wrap: anywhere; word-break: break-word; direction: ltr; text-align: start;\"><span style=\"font-weight: bold; font-style: normal; background: none;\">(9) Rest and recover</span><span style=\"font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; background: none;\">: Rest is very crucial for bodybuilding, Take sufficient rest and let your body recover.</span></p> <p class=\"q-text qu-display--block\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-bottom: 1em; overflow-wrap: anywhere; word-break: break-word; direction: ltr; text-align: start;\"><span style=\"font-weight: bold; font-style: normal; background: none;\">(10) No steroids</span><span style=\"font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; background: none;\">: Do not take steroids for bodybuilding. Instead, you can add good quality protein supplements in your diet which can help you to gradually gain muscle mass.</span></p> <p class=\"q-text qu-display--block\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-bottom: 1em; overflow-wrap: anywhere; word-break: break-word; direction: ltr; text-align: start;\"><span style=\"font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; background: none;\">Hope this helps.</span></p> <p class=\"q-text qu-display--block\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-bottom: 0px; overflow-wrap: anywhere; word-break: break-word; direction: ltr; text-align: start;\"><span style=\"font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; background: none;\">Please upvote if found helpful :)</span></p> ",
