            "html": "<p class=\"q-text qu-display--block\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-bottom: 1em; overflow-wrap: anywhere; word-break: break-word; direction: ltr; text-align: start;\"><span style=\"font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; background: none;\">I like the answers here for the most part and I'm going to carry on them just a bit further because it's fun for me.</span></p> <p class=\"q-text qu-display--block\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-bottom: 1em; overflow-wrap: anywhere; word-break: break-word; direction: ltr; text-align: start;\"><span style=\"font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; background: none;\">Progressing on strength on the following 5 basic movement patterns will create the foundation upon which the house that your future Mr. Olympia titles will be built:  The squat, the deadlift, the overhead press, the bench press, and the barbell row (or any heavy, properly executed full range of motion upper body pulling exercise).</span></p> <p class=\"q-text qu-display--block\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-bottom: 1em; overflow-wrap: anywhere; word-break: break-word; direction: ltr; text-align: start;\"><span style=\"font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; background: none;\">Slowly progressing on strength on these exercises will gradually build this foundation.  This is the only way to accomplish the goal:  gradually.  Be accepting that if you are starting now, you have some work to do before your first contest.</span></p> <p class=\"q-text qu-display--block\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-bottom: 1em; overflow-wrap: anywhere; word-break: break-word; direction: ltr; text-align: start;\"><span style=\"font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; background: none;\">Build a base of strength for approximately 6 months- 1 year (don't be bummed out by this, everyone has to do it) and then you can begin focusing on the finer nuances of body building vs. other strength training related pursuits such as strongman events, powerlifting, physique contest prep, etc...</span></p> <p class=\"q-text qu-display--block\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-bottom: 1em; overflow-wrap: anywhere; word-break: break-word; direction: ltr; text-align: start;\"><span style=\"font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; background: none;\">Do not make the same mistake that many make when they start of not focusing on the five major lifts I mentioned earlier.  I promise you'll be happy when you look back on this decision.</span></p> <p class=\"q-text qu-display--block\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-bottom: 0px; overflow-wrap: anywhere; word-break: break-word; direction: ltr; text-align: start;\"><span style=\"font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; background: none;\">And make it fun:  I can't stress this part enough.</span></p> ",
